Introduction

Short explanation that can include details such as:

  • 3-2-1 data comes in two large tables that need to be formatted down and have a death rate per 1000 live births calculated

  • This file runs some basic checks on the csv output and highlights some specific things that should manually be checked.

Configurations

The configurations are:

  • filepath for the input data: D:/coding_repos/sdg_data_updates/3-2-1_new/Example_Input/EXAMPLE_cim2020deathcohortworkbook.xlsx
  • name of the tab the data are in; England & Wales: Table_1, UK: Table_2
  • row number of the column names: E&W: 6, UK: 6
  • location of the outputs: Example_Output

Basic checks

  • no duplicates present: TRUE

Plots

Please check the plots below for any differences between the live data (which is pulled in from the sdg-data (platform) github repo) and the new data.
